Heat 2 #frying pans{} on medium high heat.

Slice the @halloumi{250%g} into 3 slices per person.

In a #small bowl{} mix the @sun-dried tomato paste{1} with the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and set aside.

Add a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} to one of the #frying pans{}, then add the @pre-cooked baby potatoes{300%g} and fry till golden, turning frequently, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of @olive oil{} to the other frying pans, then add the halloumi slices and cook until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

Once cooked, drizzle the halloumi with the @honey{30%ml} and remove the pan from the heat.

Meanwhile, slice the @ciabatta{2} in half and halve the @premium tomato mix{125%g}.

In a small bowl mix together the olive oil, @balsamic vinegar{1/2%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add to the tomatoes and @wild rocket{40%g} and mix together well.

Spread the sundried tomato mayo on the base of each ciabatta.

Top with the honeyed halloumi and the top of the ciabatta.

Serve with the crispy potatoes, salad and any remaining mayo. Enjoy!